The actor of the Russian TV series responded to the accusations of " propaganda of LGBT and feminism"
The actor of the Russian TV series "Chiki", the creators of which were accused of "propaganda of LGBT and feminism", responded to the claims about the film.
The authors " understood the sharpness of the topics raised and did not want to offend anyone," said American Stephen Thomas Ochsner in an interview with the publication "Rise".
"It seems to me that this is a story about power and general aspects of human life.
It has nothing to do with LGBT and feminism," said the actor, who played the father of a boy who changed into women's clothing.
